Heat George Foreman or panini grill. In a small bowl, combine mayonnaise and pesto; mix well. Slice flatbread lengthwise and spray one side with nonstick cooking spray. On other side of flatbread spread mayonnaise mixture then layer chicken, cucumber, tomato and cheese; replace top of bread. Grill panini sandwiches for 3 to 5 minutes, or until golden brown and center is warm. Cut in half to serve.